history.content: Unless the CS161 instructor agrees to webcast the course, enrollment in 161 can't get bigger than the room capacity of 481, even in week 3 of class. If they have, fine. If not, you should not count on the existing waitlist being accommodated although some of it will be through normal attrition.

I was wondering how the EECS two-class minimum policy works when you are waitlisted in an EECS class. 

I am currently enrolled in two EECS classes, but would like to swap one of them for CS161, which will be accommodating all students on the waitlist starting week 3. However, I was wondering if I could drop one of the EECS classes and remain on the waitlist for 161 until I get into the class and still remain in good academic standing since EECS has the two-class minimum policy if you haven't finished your degree requirements.

I would remain in the class until I get off the waitlist and swap into 161, but since they are not adding people from the waitlist until next week, I would like to drop this class now so I don't have to do it after the drop deadline this Friday.
history.subject: Enrollment Guidelines for Waitlist
